data.title: El Idrissia, Djelfa, Algeria
data.text:
El Idrissia, also known as Zenina, is a municipality in the Djelfa Province of Algeria, located at the coordinates 34.4454200 latitude and 2.5274900 longitude. It is situated in the Saharan Atlas mountain range and experiences a hot desert climate. The town has a rich history, with evidence of human habitation dating back to the Roman period. It was an important trading center during the Middle Ages and is known for its traditional architecture and cultural heritage.
